      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks that makes sense. so the inductor is basically just adding more resistance to the flow through the circuit? i was confused why the impedance is higher than just the 50 ohm resistor part.",
      "source": "evaluator",
      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "thanks that makes sense. so the inductor is basically just adding more resistance to the flow through the circuit? i was confused why the impedance is higher than just the 50 ohm resistor part.",
